137
00:10:26,981 --> 00:10:30,526
I've dug up sweet potatoes myself.

138
00:10:30,558 --> 00:10:31,498
Really?

139
00:10:31,498 --> 00:10:32,499
That was taro...

140
00:10:33,952 --> 00:10:37,893
And I got one this big.

141
00:10:37,902 --> 00:10:39,606
That's exaggerating.

142
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:42,242
Tane, what do you like?

143
00:10:43,349 --> 00:10:45,478
Pumpkin...

144
00:10:45,581 --> 00:10:47,480
Cheese...

145
00:10:48,494 --> 00:10:49,816
And pea shoots.

146
00:10:50,332 --> 00:10:51,417
Pea shoots?

147
00:10:51,739 --> 00:10:53,042
You have good taste.

148
00:10:53,753 --> 00:10:56,222
He tried it at the restaurant
where I work part-time.

149
00:10:56,542 --> 00:10:58,191
Is it a ramen place?

150
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,092
Yeah.

151
00:11:00,894 --> 00:11:02,495
What do you like, Minoru?

152
00:11:03,114 --> 00:11:05,365
Well, nothing in particular.

153
00:11:06,526 --> 00:11:08,334
So, what do you not like?

154
00:11:08,523 --> 00:11:11,571
He hates shiitake mushrooms.

155
00:11:11,599 --> 00:11:12,746
Shiitake mushrooms?

156
00:11:12,753 --> 00:11:14,590
Don't expose me.

157
00:11:14,604 --> 00:11:17,143
If you're so picky, you won't grow.

158
00:11:17,143 --> 00:11:19,290
I have already grown up, so that's okay.

159
00:11:27,782 --> 00:11:28,922
Yutaka?

160
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,759
Bro...

161
00:11:41,584 --> 00:11:43,836
He's my older brother.

162
00:11:45,230 --> 00:11:46,239
Hello.

163
00:11:48,101 --> 00:11:50,543
My new friend...

164
00:11:50,572 --> 00:11:52,445
What are you doing in a place like this?

165
00:11:52,799 --> 00:11:54,139
I'm here to buy stuff.

166
00:11:54,139 --> 00:11:56,516
Anyway, why didn't you go yesterday?

167
00:11:59,652 --> 00:12:01,354
It's Dad's 60th birthday.

168
00:12:01,450 --> 00:12:03,156
Didn't you get a message from Mom too?

169
00:12:07,569 --> 00:12:10,456
(Yukie - What about this week?
Are you not coming home?)

170
00:12:18,454 --> 00:12:21,674
I see that you still haven't
changed whatsoever.

171
00:12:24,506 --> 00:12:27,013
Fine, I'll tell them,
"You're still alive."

172
00:12:45,198 --> 00:12:47,700
Minoru, I want to use the toilet.

173
00:12:49,189 --> 00:12:51,137
Does it have to be right now?

174
00:12:52,751 --> 00:12:54,207
Jeez.

175
00:12:54,575 --> 00:12:56,842
Sorry, Yutaka. I'll be right back.

176
00:12:57,543 --> 00:12:59,555
Minoru, hurry.

177
00:12:59,555 --> 00:13:00,513
Got it.

178
00:13:00,513 --> 00:13:01,881
Hurry up.

179
00:13:07,526 --> 00:13:08,621
Yutaka.

180
00:13:09,324 --> 00:13:11,991
From now on,
you are a member of our family.

181
00:13:12,021 --> 00:13:13,593
Think of us as your real family.

182
00:13:14,449 --> 00:13:16,562
This is your home now.

183
00:13:16,956 --> 00:13:17,964
Huh?

184
00:13:18,775 --> 00:13:19,899
I won't accept that.

185
00:13:22,381 --> 00:13:23,336
Hey.

186
00:13:23,766 --> 00:13:27,220
I don't want
a little brother.

187
00:14:18,661 --> 00:14:19,592
You...

188
00:14:21,021 --> 00:14:22,562
don't even know how to eat, do you?

189
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:25,164
Yuki.

190
00:14:26,813 --> 00:14:29,268
When he's around,
the food suddenly tastes bad.

191
00:14:32,793 --> 00:14:34,707
By the way, how were your finals?

192
00:14:35,589 --> 00:14:36,709
I got the eighth place in class.

193
00:14:38,050 --> 00:14:39,612
You did a good job.

194
00:14:39,841 --> 00:14:40,913
No.

195
00:14:41,481 --> 00:14:42,938
I've dropped two places.

196
00:14:43,292 --> 00:14:45,618
But at the parents' meeting,
the teachers kept praising you.

197
00:14:56,759 --> 00:14:58,931
Yukata, I finished peeling.

198
00:14:59,786 --> 00:15:01,734
Right, great job.

199
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:05,116
Yeah, I peeled all these myself.

200
00:15:05,516 --> 00:15:06,873
That's amazing.

201
00:15:07,696 --> 00:15:09,742
Good, now, we need meat.

202
00:15:10,678 --> 00:15:12,145
We usually use pork here.

203
00:15:12,145 --> 00:15:15,448
But each family has their own ways
of picking what meat to put in curry.

204
00:15:20,253 --> 00:15:21,287
What about your family?

205
00:15:25,993 --> 00:15:27,967
I want beef.

206
00:15:28,146 --> 00:15:29,745
No, beef is expensive.

207
00:15:35,663 --> 00:15:36,769
Yutaka...

208
00:15:37,350 --> 00:15:39,405
If you put chocolate in curry,
it'll taste better.

209
00:15:39,837 --> 00:15:41,590
- Eh? Chocolate?
- Yeah.

210
00:15:41,615 --> 00:15:43,109
It's a secret flavor.

211
00:15:43,724 --> 00:15:46,145
A secret flavor?

212
00:15:56,959 --> 00:16:00,823
(Ueda)

213
00:16:15,444 --> 00:16:17,243
Bye-bye.

214
00:16:17,764 --> 00:16:19,326
It will take 15 minutes.

215
00:16:20,102 --> 00:16:21,180
That's fast.

216
00:16:21,263 --> 00:16:22,489
No, we have to put
the curry cube in first.

217
00:16:22,489 --> 00:16:23,616
Then, wait for ten minutes.

218
00:16:23,616 --> 00:16:24,484
So long.

219
00:16:25,658 --> 00:16:27,690
