00:19:47,799 --> 00:19:49,132
I mean...

281
00:19:50,496 --> 00:19:51,524
Are you okay?

282
00:19:55,394 --> 00:19:56,462
What are you referring to?

283
00:20:03,957 --> 00:20:05,805
Good night, then.

284
00:20:07,273 --> 00:20:09,041
Okay, good night.

285
00:20:58,125 --> 00:21:01,369
I see that you still haven't
changed whatsoever.

286
00:21:14,033 --> 00:21:16,008
Will Yutaka be all right?

287
00:21:16,976 --> 00:21:19,612
He didn't seem very happy.

288
00:21:21,775 --> 00:21:23,768
I'm going to bed, then.

289
00:21:23,944 --> 00:21:25,584
Okay, good night.

290
00:21:44,996 --> 00:21:47,473
It seems like our family isn't
the only one with a difficult past.

291
00:23:10,310 --> 00:23:11,123
(Next episode)
Yay!

292
00:23:11,130 --> 00:23:12,691
(Individual problem)
You never replied.

293
00:23:12,694 --> 00:23:15,361
(Different memories)
Hey, Hozumi, you don't look very happy.

294
00:23:15,361 --> 00:23:16,495
(Gentle memories about Mom)
Mom...

295
00:23:16,495 --> 00:23:17,632
(that have been vivid until now)
was a cheerful person.

296
00:23:17,632 --> 00:23:20,812
She smiled so much that
we almost forgot she was sick.

297
00:23:21,119 --> 00:23:23,487
Minoru, you're like your mother.
